<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/724> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #724" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.38.8; Diod. 16.82.1; Dion. Hal. 15.3.1; Chr. 354 (Hala III et Rutillo IIII); Fast. Hyd. (Achala et Rutilio II); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 106, 408f. While Servilius remained in Rome (Liv. 7.38.8), Marcius in Campania broke up a Roman conspiracy to seize Campanian territory (Liv. 7.38.8-39; Dion. Hal. 15.3; Frontin. Str. 1.9.1, A. Manlius; App. Samn. 1, {Gr}). On the resulting mutiny, see Dictator and Tribunes of the Plebs." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/723> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #723" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Servilius, see Fast. Cap. on 365; on that of Marcius, see Act. Tr. on 356 and 357. Diod. has {Gr}." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/718> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #718" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.28.6; Diod. 16.74.1; Chr. 354 (Rutillo III et Torquato); Fast. Hyd. (Rutilio et Torquato II), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod., Degrassi 106, 406f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/717> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #717" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Marcius, see Act. Tr. on 357 and 356; on that of Manlius, see Act. Tr. on 340." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/687> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #687" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Marcius, the first plebeian Dictator, was also the first plebeian Censor (Liv. 7.22.6-10; 10.8.8; cf. FGrH 2 B. 1153, no. 255). See Degrassi 105, 404f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/686> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #686" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Marcius, see Act. Tr. on 357 and 356. On Naevio in the Mss of Livy (7.22.10), see Conway and Walters ad loc." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/673> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #673" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.21.4; Diod. 16.52.1; Chr. 354 (Publicula et Rutillo II); Cassiod.; Degrassi 105, 404f. Marcius may be the author of the Lex Marcia adversus faeneratores (Gaius 4.23). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 37, no. 9." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/672> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #672" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Marcius, see Fast. Cap. 357 and 356; Diod. reads {Gr}." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/660> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #660" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The first plebeian Dictator (Liv. 7.17.6). Celebrated a triumph for a victory over Etruscan and Faliscan forces (Liv. 7.17.6-9, cf. 10.8.8, and 37.10; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540; Eutrop. 2.5; Oros. 3.6.3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/659> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #659" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Marcius' name, see Act. Tr., on that of Plautius, Fast. Cap. for 358." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/653> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #653" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.16.1; Diod. 16.28.1; Chr. 354 (Rutillo et Capitolino); Fast. Hyd. (Rustico et Capitolino); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; on Marcius, Act. Tr., name entire. See Degrassi 105, 402f. Manlius held command at Falerii, and carried (while in camp at Sutrium) a bill to establish the five per cent tax on manumission (Liv. 7.16; cf. 27.10.11; cf. Cic. Att. 2.16.1). Marcius celebrated a triumph over Privernum (Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540; cf. Dion. Hal. 14.13 [23], a story better referred to 329). The passage of the bill in the camp led to a tribunicial bill to prohibit assemblies away from Rome (Liv. 7.16.8)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10155> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10155" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Tusceis. MRR I.123, Itgenshorst p. 264, Rich no. 60." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10154> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10154" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Privernatibus. MRR I.122, Itgenshorst p. 264, Rich no. 59." .
